AgentForce Infotech - Development Environment Setup

To set up your development environment at AgentForce Infotech, follow these steps:

1. Install required tools (IT team pre-installs most, but verify):
   - Docker Desktop (version 24.0 or higher) - Download from internal software portal
   - Node.js (version 20.x LTS) - Use nvm for version management
   - Python 3.12 (use pyenv for version management)
   - Git (configure with your agentforce.com email)
   - VS Code with AgentForce extensions pack (shared via IT)

2. Clone the AgentForce repositories:
   git clone https://gitlab.agentforce.internal/backend/phoenix-api.git
   git clone https://gitlab.agentforce.internal/frontend/phoenix-web.git
   cd phoenix-api

3. Set up environment variables:
   Contact Anjali Mehta (DevOps - anjali.mehta@agentforce.com) for:
   - Database connection strings (PostgreSQL 15)
   - Redis cluster endpoints
   - AWS S3 bucket credentials
   - API keys for third-party services
   
   Copy .env.example to .env and fill in the credentials provided

4. Install dependencies:
   cd phoenix-api && pip install -r requirements.txt
   cd ../phoenix-web && npm install

5. Run local services using AgentForce docker-compose:
   docker-compose -f docker-compose.local.yml up -d
   This starts: PostgreSQL, Redis, Elasticsearch, and RabbitMQ
   
   Start backend: python manage.py runserver 0.0.0.0:8000
   Start frontend: cd phoenix-web && npm run dev

6. Access the application:
   Frontend: http://localhost:5173 (Vite dev server)
   Backend API: http://localhost:8000
   API Docs: http://localhost:8000/api/docs (Swagger)
   Admin Panel: http://localhost:8000/admin (credentials from Anjali)

7. Run initial database migrations:
   python manage.py migrate
   python manage.py loaddata initial_data.json

For issues, contact #agentforce-dev-support Slack channel or email devops@agentforce.com.
